accuracy and efficiency of root cause localization. We evaluate the
effect of the termination strategy by analyzing how the accuracy
and time of root cause localization change with the hyperparameters. In Section 4.4.2, we configured two parameters, ğ›¼ and ğ›½, in
the reward function of the Q-learning algorithm. The ğ›¼ and ğ›½ respectively represent the complexity of the causal graph and the
accuracy of the RCA.
